# LLM eval backend (@cursor/sdk) ‚Äî `declarative` strategy

Scaffolded by `zoto-eval-system`. This directory is stamped into your repo
at `{evalsDir}/_llm/`. Everything here is yours ‚Äî feel free to edit, but
the diff-aware updater (`/z-eval-update`) will regenerate generated eval
cases (those with `_meta.generated: true`) when covered targets drift.

## Layout

- `runner.ts` ‚Äî discovers cases, validates the enriched shape, runs them, writes `llm.yml` + per-case logs.
- `update.ts` ‚Äî surgical diff engine. Mirrors `scripts/eval-update.ts` inside the plugin.
- `compare.ts` ‚Äî emits the `/canvas` hand-off dataset for cross-run analysis.
- `case.ts` ‚Äî typed eval-case loader. Owns `validateEnriched(case)`.
- `_user-case-guards.ts` ‚Äî canonical `_meta.generated` predicates (subtask 09).
- `graders/` ‚Äî `contains`, `regex`, `tool-called`, `llm-judge`.
- `metrics.ts` ‚Äî tokens, duration, verbosity, accuracy, confidence.
- `writer.ts` ‚Äî schema-valid YAML + per-case logs.
- `result.schema.json` ‚Äî JSON Schema for `llm.yml` (copied from plugin templates).

## Enriched `evals.json` shape (subtask 10)

The `declarative` strategy reads cases that the LLM analyser
(subtask 04) produced. Each case **must** carry:

```jsonc
{
  "id": "case-1",
  // Realistic user/agent turn, never a placeholder. Short tokens
  // ("TODO", "...", "n/a") and the literal "<placeholder>" marker
  // are rejected before the SDK is touched.
  "prompt": "/z-eval-create ‚Äî bootstrap a fresh repo from scratch.",

  // ‚â• 1 behavioural assertion. Shape-only checks are NOT enough for
  // the declarative runner ‚Äî every entry must be a non-empty string.
  "assertions": [
    "Replies confirm `evals/` was created with the static + LLM scaffold.",
    "Mentions `manifest.yml` and the append-only history."
  ],

  // Optional. Per-case overlays applied AFTER the baseline copy
  // (`evals/fixtures/baseline/`). Keep this list short ‚Äî only when
  // the analyser justified the extra files.
  "fixtures": { "files": [{ "path": "extra.md", "content": "..." }] },

  // Optional graders. Re-uses contains/regex/tool-called/llm-judge.
  "graders": [{ "type": "contains", "needle": "manifest.yml" }],

  "_meta": {
    "generated": true,
    "source_hash": "<sha256 of normalised SKILL.md>",
    "last_updated": "2026-05-04T00:00:00Z",
    "generated_by": "zoto-create-evals",
    // REQUIRED on every generated case. The runner rejects the case
    // (and exits 1) if this block is missing or malformed.
    "primitive_analysis": {
      "source_hash": "<64-char hex>",
      "analysed_at": "2026-05-04T00:00:00Z",
      "analyser_version": "1.x.y",
      "summary": "Short natural-language summary the analyser produced."
    }
  }
}
```

User-authored cases (`_meta` missing, or `_meta.generated === false`)
are NEVER touched by the updater and are exempt from the
`primitive_analysis` requirement ‚Äî they still must ship a non-placeholder
prompt and ‚â• 1 assertion.

## Rejection rules ‚Äî `validateEnriched(case)`

The runner gates every case through `validateEnriched(case)` before
constructing the `Agent`. Rejected cases print their reason on stderr and
the runner returns exit code 1 BEFORE any SDK call:

| Rule | Reason on fail |
|------|----------------|
| `prompt` is a non-placeholder string ‚â• 8 chars | `prompt is empty` / `prompt is too short` / `prompt contains placeholder marker` |
| `assertions[]` is non-empty and every entry is a non-empty string | `case has no assertions; declarative runner requires ‚â•1` |
| Generated case carries a complete `_meta.primitive_analysis` block | `_meta.primitive_analysis missing on a generated case` / `_meta.primitive_analysis missing required fields: ‚Ä¶` |

This makes drift cheap to detect: any case that lost its analyser
payload (e.g. via a mid-flight schema migration) trips the runner before
billing the SDK.

## Running

```bash
pnpm run eval:list                   # list discovered cases
pnpm run eval:full                   # static + LLM, gated on CURSOR_API_KEY
pnpm run eval:llm                    # LLM only (still gated, subtask 12 owns this alias)
pnpm run eval:llm:declarative -- --full
                                     # subtask 10 entry point ‚Äî declarative runner only
pnpm run eval:update                 # rediscovery dry-run
pnpm run eval:update:check           # CI gate (exit 2 on critical drift)
pnpm run eval:compare run-a run-b    # /canvas hand-off
```

## Two-gate startup

The runner refuses to start without both:

1. `--full` passed on the CLI.
2. `CURSOR_API_KEY` in the environment.

Both gates "skip + exit 0" rather than fail loudly so dry runs in CI /
dev sandboxes don't break the build. CI scripts that want a hard
"must run" gate use `--full` explicitly and surface the skip line.

### Sourcing `CURSOR_API_KEY` from `.env`

`runner.ts` imports `dotenv/config` at startup, so values in `.env` at the
repo root flow into `process.env` automatically. Standard dotenv precedence
applies: anything already exported in your shell wins over `.env`.

```bash
cp .env.example .env       # .env is gitignored ‚Äî never commit it
# edit .env, set CURSOR_API_KEY=...
pnpm run eval:full
```

`.env.example` ships as a placeholder via `/z-eval-create` and is never
overwritten by the scaffolder.

## Model precedence

1. `--model <id>` flag.
2. `ZOTO_EVAL_MODEL` env var.
3. `config.llm.model.id` from `.zoto/eval-system/config.yml`.

Allowed ids: `composer-2`, `opus-4.6`, `sonnet`.

## Per-case logs & report

Each case writes `{evalsDir}/_runs/<run-id>/logs/<case>.log` containing:

- The final prompt.
- The raw response.
- All grader reports.
- Soft metrics (tokens, duration, verbosity, accuracy, confidence).

The aggregated suite report lands at `{evalsDir}/_runs/<run-id>/llm.yml`
and validates against `templates/schema/result.schema.json`. Subtask 12's
orchestrator merges this with `static.yml` into the top-level `report.yml`.

`/z-eval-compare` drill-down links to the per-case log files.
